      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AHH CHOUX (3) finished off strongly over this trip at Ascot last time out to be 2.3L off the winner most recently. She looks well placed here on recent efforts and CJP remaining in the saddle is a positive sign. Racing in good order and can go one better this time around. RENOVATION SHOW (2) bolted in two back at Albany but couldn't repeat the dose last time out when beaten 1.3L. Rises in weight here, but takes on a slightly easier assignment today and he's shown versatility in his past couple. Can feature in the finish again. SHAMISTER (6) stuck on well when beaten 1.8L at Ascot last time out after a good win at Narrogin two back. The rise in trip looks ideal now and his NSW form at this trip stacks up. Can make his presence felt. LIEN HYPHEN (1) won by 1.6L last start in easier company and draws nicely. Can make an impression. IDODOMYA (4) is next best.",
